text.tspan: Boys Love’s main characters are set to be attractive and the
story focuses on the interactions between characters. For
each panel, the author focuses on facial expression and pos
tures of characters. The backgrounds are usually not drawn
or just covered by shades. Author Tachibana uses this tech
nique to highlight the interactions between characters. Also
good-looking men are the selling points, zooming in on their
looks accomplish to satisfy readers. The style of drawing on
characters are not realistic but also not cartoony. It’s in a fan
tasied way to magnify the attractive looking.
There is hardly any intensive action scenes. It composes
small actions and conversations. Thus the pace of manga is
fairly slow. Author uses change of view to reflect the emotion
al state and reactions of each character.
Boys Love represents an art style of Yaoi that is similar to
shojo manga. The art style of it represents reads attractive
and dreamy characters. In addition, the story focuses on the
development of emotional bond between characters. It does
not include much sexual contents but rather creates a ro
mantic relationship.
